A. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Design Low-Level Design for TinyURL (URL Shortener Service).

Requirements:

Given a long URL, generate a short URL (e.g., https://tiny.url/abc123).
When user accesses the short URL, redirect to the original long URL.
Support basic analytics (number of clicks).
Same long URL should always return the same short URL (idempotent).
Optional: Support custom short aliases.
URLs should support expiration.

Constraints:

Short code should be short (6–8 characters).
High read traffic (redirects).
In-memory implementation is fine for LLD

