C. 6 MANDATORY STEPS FOR LLD DESIGN

1. Clarify requirements

=> Functional: Shorten long URL, redirect short URL, basic click analytics, support custom alias.
=> Non-Functional: Fast redirection, handle collisions gracefully, reasonable scale (millions of URLs).
=> Assumptions: Single instance, in-memory storage, default 1-year expiry.
=> Edge Cases: Empty URL, collision, expired URL, custom alias conflict.

2. Identify entities and relationships

=> Main Entities: UrlMapping, TinyUrlService
=> Relationships :
One shortCode maps to one longUrl (bidirectional mapping needed).
UrlMapping contains longUrl, shortCode, clickCount, expiry.

