5. Explain the LLD verbally

=> I am using Base62 encoding with a global counter instead of random generation.
=> This ensures short codes are unique and distributed well
=> I maintain two maps — shortToMapping for fast redirection and longToShort for idempotency
=> On shortening, if the long URL already exists, I return the existing short code. It ensures idempotency

6. Discuss trade-offs and alternatives

=> Base62 counter vs Random: Base62 is deterministic and avoids collision checks in most cases.
=> Two maps: Necessary for O(1) operations on both shorten and redirect.
=> In-memory vs Persistent: Fine for LLD. In production, combine with Redis cache + database.

